<button class="accordion">What is medication management therapy?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Medication management therapy (MTM) is a treatment system used by doctors and pharmacists. It is to ensure that patients are receiving optimal therapeutic outcomes for the prescription medications that they may be taking.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is medication management therapy used to cover?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Medication management therapy used to cover a broad range of professional activities, such as:</p>
<li>Performing patient assessments or a comprehensive review of prescriptions and their possible interaction or side effects</li>
<li>Formulating both short and long term medication treatment plans</li>
<li>Monitoring the safety and efficacy of any prescription medication plans</li>
<li>Ensuring directional or instruction-based compliance through patient education</li>
<li>Better documentation and communication between MTM service providers to maintain a high standard of care among medical professionals</li>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is psychiatric medication management?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>It is when psychiatrists or psychiatric practitioners give psychiatric medication management and assessment to patients. If you are not sure if medications are the best option for you, a psychiatrist or practitioner can be of great assistance to you to explore your options. There are a lot of unknowns when it comes to available medications. However, understanding how a professional can help you, and learning what medication management means will help ease all of the unknowns. Also being aware of what to expect with a psychiatric assessment will reduce your anxiety about it.</p>
</div>
